    "tutorial_body": "<p>A <b>profile</b> is the collection of all the configurations found in the <code>Settings</code> pages.</p><br><p>You can have multiple profiles but only one can be active at a time. You can switch between them with a <i>tap</i>, and edit them via <i>double-tap</i> or <i>long-tap</i></p><br><p>One use case is to have multiple defaults for the <b>transaction-form</b>: one for your daily usage and one for your vacation. The vacation profile can have a different source account, or have a tag called \"Vacation August 2025\" auto-applied. This makes it easy to see your total expense by that tag.</p>"
